The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 2.6 percent to 21,393.59. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 2.1 percent to 2,798.96.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, plunged 10 percent
to 62 cents, the lowest since October 2010, after U.S. stocks
and copper slumped in  New York , said Estefany Castillo, an
analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, slid 4.5 percent to 63 cents.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peruâ€™s biggest copper
producer, fell 4.5 percent to $31.05.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, dropped 4.5 percent to 85 centimos
after crude declined for a fifth session in New York.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural-gas
producer with operations in Peru, dropped 4.3 percent to $1.10.  To contact the reporter on this story:
